  • I want to return an item

    Find the item you'd like to return and select Return this item from the More actions drop-down menu.

    If the item is damaged or doesn't match the listing description, you're covered under the eBay Money Back Guarantee.

    If you've changed your mind and no longer want an item, you can still open a request, but the seller doesn't have to accept it.

  • Who pays for return postage?

    If there's a problem with an item, the seller is responsible for paying return postage costs. If you change your mind about a purchase, you may be required to pay return postage. Learn more about paying for returns - opens in new window or tab.

  • How do I cancel my order?

    You'll need to contact the seller to ask them to cancel your order. Go to the More actions drop-down menu next to the item and select Contact seller.

    If the item has already been posted, you'll need to wait to receive it and then start a return.
